doc_summary_long: Four central European countries are prepared to veto any Brexit deal agreed between the UK and the European Union that restricts their citizens' rights to live and work in Britain, the prime minister of Slovakia has said. In a stark reminder of the challenge Britain faces at the negotiating table, Robert Fico said Hungary, Poland, the Czech Republic and Slovakia - the Visegrad or V4 group - would not hesitate to block any accord that threatened the key EU principle of free movement of workers. Brexit vote was rejection of economic status quo, says Jeremy Corbyn.
doc_summary_short: Four central European countries are prepared to veto any Brexit deal agreed between the UK and the European Union that restricts their citizens' rights to live and work in Britain, the prime minister of Slovakia has said.
doc_title: EU states set to veto any Brexit deal threatening free movement.
